	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				First off,the enchanter pet is NOT the weakest... it simply has the least hitpoints of the available pets. It is also the fastest, and with your own buffs, you can turn it into a buzzsaw with quickness, strength and other such lines. The problem is you can't control it and it dies easy due to low hp. Also, the pet will do full damage without augmentation by a weapon of some sort, unlike magicians and necros.<BR>
<BR>
Watch a lev 16 enchanter and a lev 16 magician go at a mob. You will probably notice 2 things... 1)the enchanter pet is on the order of 40% faster, and 2) the magician pet can take on the order of 40% more damage, and tends to dish out a bit more with spells and such.<BR>
<BR>
Second, why are you using a pet with multiple mobs as an enchanter? It's very hard to get the pet to attack the mob that you debuffed in a group.<BR>
<BR>
A better tactic: Mez one of the mobs. this brings two after you. color flux, mez another. Root or wait for the flux to recharge for the last one. Tashan, charm. Send the sucker after his bud. Aid your new pet until mob is dead. Do it again on the 2nd mob. at this point the charmed pet is so beat up it can hardly move. <BR>
<BR>
At this point, you have a choice. Tuck and run, or kill the pet 1 on 1. I opt for the tuck, due to the fact that you are probably low on mana at this point.<BR>
<BR>
Give the pet a &quot;/pet sit down&quot; command. The pet will say &quot;changing position master&quot;. Except, instead of sitting, the pet will start to wander off. KEEP THE PET TARGETED, and walk in the opposite direction of the pet. Meditate. PAY ATTENTION as to when the charm wears off. As the mob gets in range, mem blur, zip zap, ur fine, and you just got xp for 2 yellow/black/blue mobs. Not bad. Beats the hell out of trying to control your uncontrollable pet!<BR>
<BR>
-Fringe<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
